<p>LG gas dryer valve replacement costs <strong>$280–450 total</strong> in Los Angeles, Orange County, and Ventura County — $280–340 for solenoid coils only, $380–450 for the full valve assembly. OEM parts, igniter check included, gas supply verified before we start, soap leak test after installation, and 1-year warranty. The $65 diagnostic fee is waived when you approve the repair. A properly maintained LG gas dryer runs 12–15 years — most gas valve calls we get are fixable, not reasons to buy new.</p>
